Response to Tom Dier<br><br>
Tom, I stand corrected. You are right, and I was in error.  I did not intend my e mail dialogue to get so righteous, nor did I want to be name calling, and your response brought that home right between<br>
my cyber eyes. <br><br>
Being right is not important, what is important is<br>
making sure that another viet nam NEVER happens again.  That another almost civil war within our boundaries doesn not happen again.  I have seen every movie about nam with a strange sense of &quot;there but for the grace of god was I&quot;.  No, bedpans won't match firefights, and I had to chose where I would serve, because I won't run from my country.  Being a medic, going into the jungle with a bandage and not a gun, maybe the wierdist folly or the purist believer, I don't know which.  I would think that that is the ultimate in belief.  <br><br>
Again, thanks, your are right, perhaps this is a beginning in mutual respect and coming together for all of us, protesting patriots and victimized soldiers.    Yes, by the way, I am a shrink, but<br>
burned out and no longer doing therapy. Guess this is my couch now.<br><br>
Spatz
